The most likely name is a brazier — a portable container (bowl or pan) for holding burning coals or embers. Braziers were often set into or carried inside wicker or wooden cases for handling and insulation.

Depending on context you might also hear:
- coal scuttle or coal hod — a bucket for carrying coal/embers;
- foot‑warmer or bed‑warmer — a small pan of embers placed under feet or in a bed (often housed in a wooden/wicker box);
- chafing dish — for keeping food warm, sometimes using hot coals.

